page.title: 06ECOLOGY
page.content: This area is mainly rural on the outskirts of residential land.There is still farmland here.The main habitats are:1{hedge_line lanes,}made up of {brambles,oaktrees,nettles,ivy,dogwood {road,holly,hawthorn,rowan}and dead elms left by the recent outbreak of {Dutch Elm Disease.}Here can be found {bullfinches,long-tailed tits,doves, {kestrels,woodpeckers,bank voles, {rabbits,bats,butterflies,screech {beetles,dor beetles,cockchafers, {sawflies,ladybirds,rove beetles {hoverflies,gall wasps,crane flies, {cross-spiders,wolf-spiders,slugs}& {snails.}The second important ecological area is:{Dinton Pastures Country Park. This includes 4 lakes that were formed where gravel has been extracted from the{Thames Valley}and includes the {River Loddon}and the{Embrook.
